The paper discusses the creation of a large-scale and multilingual knowledge extraction corpus using NLP techniques, which makes it highly relevant to the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The dataset is based on DBpedia, a structured knowledge base, which makes it relevant to the field of databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for knowledge extraction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
